  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/feats/persuasive.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl154_LabelType\">Through pacts with eldritch beings or a simple quirk of circumstance, your voice has an uncanny rapport with those swept up in madness.</span></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl154_LabelType\">Once per day as an immediate action, you can issue a command to a confused creature within 30 feet. This allows the creature to immediately reroll on the confused condition table, and you can pick which of the two actions&mdash;the action of its initial roll or that of the reroll&mdash;the creature takes. Confused creatures do not need to understand you for this trait to take effect.</span></p>",
